Today we learned about the Random module and Inheritance in Object-Oriented Programming (OOP). The mentor explained how the random module can be used to generate random values in Python and how it is useful for developing simple games. We learned how to use random numbers to create games such as Number Guessing and Stone-Paper-Scissors, making programs more interactive and interesting.
In the second part of the session, the mentor introduced the concept of Inheritance in Python. We learned how one class can inherit the properties and methods of another class, allowing code to be reused and making programs more organized. The mentor explained parent and child classes with practical examples and demonstrated how inheritance works in Python.
After the explanation, we practiced several programs based on the random module and inheritance. These exercises helped us understand how to implement these concepts in real Python programs and improved our understanding of Object-Oriented Programming.
